[49m[38;5;10m+    196[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    197[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ## General Architecture Pattern
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    198[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    199[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A care-coordination assistant decomposes into ten logical stages: episode initialization with care-plan ingestion, multi-system longitudinal-store hydration, channel entry with disclosure, input safety screening with continuous criticality screening, identity-and-context loading with episode-aware retrieval, conversation handling with episode-protocol-grounded responses, output safety screening with scope verification, escalation routing to human navigators when applicable, care-team reporting with consent enforcement, and audit logging with coordination-specific retention discipline. The cross-cutting concerns from recipes 11.1 through 11.8 carry forward; this recipe adds five new ones (multi-system integration as architectural primitive, episode-and-event-driven workflow modeling, referral-status reconciliation discipline, prior-auth-state-machine discipline, and caregiver-context support with consent management).
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    200[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    201[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    202[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ┌────────── EPISODE INITIALIZATION + CARE PLAN INGESTION ─────┐
