[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    627[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ```
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    628[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    629[0m:[38;5;10m[49m A few cross-cutting design points specific to the care-coordination assistant.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    630[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    631[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Multi-system integration as architectural primitive.** Each integration has its own authentication, its own data model, its own reliability profile, and its own data-sharing posture. The integration layer is the architectural backbone, not an afterthought. Per-integration health monitoring, retry-and-backoff handling, and graceful degradation when an integration is unreachable are explicit.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    632[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    633[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Episode-and-event-driven workflow modeling.** The assistant is event-driven, not just conversation-driven. Upstream events (discharge, referral-placed, prior-auth-submitted, status-changed, lab-resulted, missed-appointment) trigger workflows that may include patient-facing conversation, care-team alerts, or both. The event bus and the episode-protocol corpus are first-class architectural concerns.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    634[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    635[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Episode-protocol corpus governance.** The episode-protocol corpus (post-discharge cardiac, post-discharge orthopedic, new-cancer-diagnosis, high-risk-OB, transition-of-care, etc.) is owned by care-management leadership, reviewed before adoption, reviewed annually, and re-reviewed when material updates are made. Each protocol has defined coordination tasks, expected timelines, escalation criteria, and patient-facing content references.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    636[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    637[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Referral-status reconciliation discipline.** The assistant maintains the institution's view of referral status, recognizes when partner-system data may be stale, may prompt the patient for status they have learned directly, and escalates to a human navigator to resolve partner-system gaps when needed.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    638[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    639[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Prior-auth-state-machine discipline.** The prior-auth state machine is encoded explicitly with patient-facing and care-team-facing messages per state. The LLM does not invent the states.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    640[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    641[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Caregiver-context support with consent management.** Caregivers are first-class participants where the patient has consented. The architecture has explicit caregiver support, with consent-gated context, persona-aware framing, and audit trails recording whose interaction is being logged.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    642[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    643[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Cross-organization data-sharing posture.** The assistant operates within institutional data-sharing agreements with partner organizations. Cross-organization data is surfaced only within the consent and the data-sharing-agreement scope.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    644[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    645[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Citation and provenance discipline.** Every coordination claim is grounded in a cited source (the referral-management-system record, the prior-auth-system record, the EHR record, the scheduling-system record). When source data is stale, the assistant says so explicitly.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    646[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    647[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Conservative-bias-default policy.** When the assistant is uncertain, when partner-system data is stale, when the conversation drifts toward clinical topics, when caregiver consent scope is ambiguous, the response defaults to "let me connect you with a person."
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    648[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    649[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Per-cohort monitoring is non-negotiable.** Engagement rate, escalation rate, referral-completion rate, prior-auth-resolution rate, citation-coverage rate, and patient satisfaction vary by language, channel, episode type, age cohort, sex, social-determinant flags. Per-cohort dashboards reviewed by care-management leadership, operations, compliance, and patient-experience teams.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    650[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    651[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Disaster-recovery topology.** When the institution's primary EHR, the referral-management system, the prior-auth-management system, the scheduling system, or any partner integration is unreachable, the assistant degrades gracefully. The minimum behavior is "I'm having trouble reaching the system right now; I'll try again in a few minutes, and if it's urgent your care team can be reached through the help button." The graceful degradation paths are exercised in tabletop drills.
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    652[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
